# Main Goal

The main goal is to build a **modern ecommerce platform for selling clothes**.

The application must support:

- Product catalog with variants (size, color, materials)
- Shopping cart
- Orders and payments
- User accounts and addresses
- Discounts and promotions
- Admin product management
- Support system
- Clean and scalable architecture

---

# Database Architecture Understanding

This ecommerce database is structured into the following main domains:

## Users Domain

Handles authentication and user-related data.

### User
Represents customers and admins.

- User can have multiple addresses
- User has one cart
- User can create multiple orders
- User can create support requests

### UserAddress
Stores shipping addresses.

- One user → many addresses
- One address → many orders
- Supports default address

---

## Catalog Domain

Handles product organization and filtering.

### Brand
Product brand (Nike, Adidas, etc.)

### Category
Hierarchical categories

Example:
- Men
  - Shirts
  - Pants

Supports parent-child categories.

### Color
Product color variants

### Size
Product size variants

Example:
- S
- M
- L
- XL

### Material
Product materials

Example:
- Cotton
- Polyester
- Denim

### Tag
Used for filtering products

Example:
- New
- Trending
- Sale

### Discount
Product discount configuration

- Percentage discount
- Start date
- End date

---

## Product Domain

Core ecommerce models.

### Product

Main product entity:

- Name
- Description
- Price
- Brand
- Category
- Discount

Relationships:

- Product → Variants
- Product → Images
- Product → Tags
- Product → Materials

---

### ProductVariant

Handles clothing variants:

Example:
- Shirt
  - Red / M
  - Red / L
  - Blue / M
  - Blue / L

Each variant has:

- Color
- Size
- Stock
- SKU
- Optional price override

---

### ProductImage

Product images with ordering.

Supports:

- Multiple images
- Gallery
- Main image

---

## Cart Domain

### Cart

Each user has one cart.

### CartItem

Cart contains:

- Product variant
- Quantity

---

## Orders Domain

### Order

Represents customer purchase.

Contains:

- User
- Address
- Total
- Status

Order Status:

- Pending
- Confirmed
- Shipped
- Delivered
- Cancelled

---

### OrderItem

Each product inside order:

- Product variant
- Quantity
- Price snapshot

---

## Payments Domain

### Payment

Handles payment processing.

Payment Methods:

- Credit Card
- Debit Card
- PayPal
- Bank Transfer

Payment Status:

- Pending
- Completed
- Failed
- Refunded

---

## Support Domain

### SupportRequest

Customer support tickets.

- Subject
- Message
- Status

Status:

- Open
- In Progress
- Resolved
- Closed

---

## Logs Domain

### Log

System logs.

Used for:

- Debugging
- Monitoring
- Error tracking

Log levels:

- INFO
- ERROR
- WARN
- DEBUG

---

